<br>
Verant is basically monkeying around with like 15 things at once. Sadly, that has unforseen (to them, apparently) consiquences.<br>
<br>
1) Pets use owner's resist (if higher than their innate) and owner's level. This still works, kinda. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> BUG:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Mage pets, that had ultra high resistance to one kind of element seem to have major issues with a highly buffed mage, and lose that ultra high resistance/immunity.<br>
<br>
2) Resist numbers are now a shallower gradient. Meaning, it takes more resist points to achieve the same effect. Mobs and PC's all over got a universal increase in magical vulnerability with this change. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Bug/Failed Consideration:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> The game was geared, at lower levels, to have level mean a lot more than resist values, and even then, the resist values of attainable items are pathetic compared to what's needed. All resist gear items now have become degraded in their usefullness.<br>
<br>
It's point #2 that really screwed with our pets, but the Bug in #1 really hurts as well. Both together have seriously collapsed the concept of Mage pets having specific ultra high resist/immunity to an element. Fire pets get eatten by fire spells easily, now.<br>
<br>
